content.detailedDescription:
I'm a trucker driver and traveling west bound on i-10 in maran az. it was 
about 12:30 pm az time. when i happened to look up and seen this pretty good
sized object falling from our atmosphere. first i thought space shuttle 
cause of the size...Maybe the size of an aleve pill. the weird part about this all is that the cloud trail wrapped around the whole object unlike planes with cloud trails coming from the wings. the cloud trail was about thick as a #2 pencil lead and only left a trail 1 1/2 inch long. now when i 
the object was about an aleve pill i mean that was the space the cloud trail wrapped around. i pulled my camera out to try and zoom in to take a pic  ut that was pretty difficult to do cause i was driving and had no place to pull of quickly with an 18wheeler. but from what i could see from my camera was that there was no object inside this cloud trail. what got me to notice this o ject not cause of the size but how it was falling....Falling straight down. it fell for a good 5secs then you could see it level off and was traveling the same direction i was. i say it flew in that direction till it looked like a pimple then took a hard 90° towards the north. then i lost sight of it
content.summary: Asprin size with cloud trails that wrapped around it

content.detailedDescription: I was leaving the ranch out of the main gate when something to my right caught my eye,it was a yellowish object that was very bright right above the tree line,it was slowly rising straight up,getting brighter and turning to an orange color,i pulled over to get my phone to take some pictures ,a car drove by at the same time and slowed down to almost a stop,i figured he saw the thing to(tail lights can barely be seen at the bottom of first picture),i started to take a picture when i noticed another object way above and behind it,but moving about the same speed(i caught it on the video ,but not in photos). the  object seemed to be on a flight pattern like an airplane,but then it would stop completely,go down to the treeline,go back the same direction it came from,but then continue on its course,it was maybe 100-200 feet away and made no noise whatsoever,and was so bright i really couldn't see an outline,my phone camera would take a picture then go back to the home screen and be non responsive for a couple of seconds which is not the norm,as the thing passes me up i notice the other one falling behind,than the main one i was watching speed up and seemed to change from a glowing ball to something that looked more like ,i don't know something more defined and had red is lights that seemed to be in sync,and then as it got farther away looked almost like airplane lights so much i wondered if when i was messing with my phone that it might have vanished and a plane was passing by and i was not the same object. the one above it was still there just above me in the sky and as i was trying to see what was up with my phone when i looked back up it was gone,as was the car that was passing by.
content.summary: I saw a bright light,that got brighter,changed color

content.detailedDescription: I was walking home from a friend's house in the middle of the street. it was eerily quiet and uncomfortably silent which was broken by the sounds of a helicopter approaching fast and low. while scanning the sky in the direction of the sound i witness an orange orb appear from behind the tree line immediately pursued by a full throttle low flying helicopter.The object kept a straight path until out of view as did the helicopter crossing over the horizon.I immediately knew i was seeing something incredible. my initial reaction was pure terror and crying while running home to share my story.
content.summary: Black helicopter aggressively pursuing orange light across the town. helicopters altitude was uncomfortably low.

content.detailedDescription:
We were on our way to my older brothers fiancée house.
i was 14 at the time and had become interested in astronomy  year before so at night my eyes were usually looking at the sky.
we were on our way to the car, i was looking up and thought i had found a constellation but one of the stars in it was moving slowly. no sound. there was a few inches of snow on the ground. it was a beautiful, clear and quiet night.
i looked more closely and realized i was looking at a triangle shaped object with a few lights on the bottom. it was moving slowly.
i couldn't tell its size but it was very clear against the night sky.
i'm thinking it was more then 500 ft away and i could not figure out how big it was.
i had it in perfect view for about 30 seconds to a minute when my dad called me to get in the car. i then ran to the car and told them to get out and look at the object, taking my eyes off of it for about 30 seconds. 
then when i tried to find it again, it was gone!!!!!!
i started telling people what i saw and most reactions were of disbelief so from then on i kept it to myself!!!
this was my only ufo i have ever had the pleasure of seeing in my 70 years!!!!!!
content.summary: Triangle object with a few lights

content.detailedDescription: Sometime in the late summer of 1999 myself and three friends stopped in the middle of the country south of trilla illinois we began to mess with a light that we had seen for a couple of years this light was erratic and move in strange ways across the sky i had a new mag light and we decided to use it to mess with the light in the sky when we shine the flashlight at the light in the sky the light in the sky came much closer we could see the light between us and the treeline behind it.  as we noticed it was in the field in front of us the light became very dim and the craft moved toward us at a very slow rate of speed the craft made absolutely no noise and flew directly over our heads the craft was close enough i could have hit it throwing a rock.  the craft flew about the same distance away from us to the south then absolutely and completely disappeared my friends and i were so scared that we jumped into our vehicle and took off as fast as we could toward home.
content.summary: Myself and two friends saw a light in the sky over a two year period which made eratic movements.  we taunted this light with a new 3 cell mag light.  the light then turned out and a triangle was present.  the triangle flew over us at 3 miles per hour

content.detailedDescription:
On march 1 2016 i was disposing trash at approximately 9 pm. the lighs was what i noticed at first. they where white and formed a cheveron shape that allowed me to  notice the shape of the object. 
 it was very large as it passed beside me. i was near the tower, so i knew it was high but not too high as for me not to get an idea how large this object was. 
 the planes at terminal 4 where lined up and nothing was moving. i was in total disbelief that it was happening! it made no noise at all. as i observed the object travel ne over to the skytrain station i lost view of the lights then the object. 
it was darker than the sky with the exception of the lights eminating from the bottom it was black. 
i didn't feel any thing but shock as i pondered what had just took place. the lights where i was dumping the trash had a nonfunctional light. it was not changed till a few days later. 
 so i knew a glare would not have effect what i had seen. the tug i had used to drive there was off so no other light source was close enough to hamper my vision. this event lasted just about 5 minutes of so. i felt calm and no sense of danger or aprihention afterwards. just a sense of wonder and amazment that something so huge could travel in the air and not make any noise. thank you that is the end of my report. 4.6.2016 5:09am

content.detailedDescription: It's april 5th, 2016. 5:06am and i cannot return back to my usual sleeping pattern. at 3:37am i woke up to use the bathroom. as i was sitting on the toilet i looked out the window to the right of me and saw blue lights zipping back forth horizontally across the road from where i live. they were so blue it was impossible not to see them. my first glimpse took my breath away. i had forgotten how to breathe and i just sat there shaking with fear. i'm in awe as to what i'm witnessing in this moment. even as i am writing this i am still shaking with fear. there were two blue lights hovering back and forth as fast as a lightning strike would hit the ground. that was as fast as they were moving. i'm terrified! this is not the first time i have seen them out in this area. i'm not sure what to do. i'm scared for myself and my family. oh and get this, i live between 4 cattle farms and the area that these lights were hovering were over at the one farm several hundred feet away from my house. coincidence? i only wish i could have gotten video feed of this experience. i know this won't be the last time i will see this but i really wish that it would be. i can't just be the only one who is seeing this out here.
content.flightPath: Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: I've never been this scared. the lights were too close this time...

content.detailedDescription:
my two boys and i were driving home at 10 pm on a wednesday night from an activity.    directly in front of us we saw three very bright objects that were in the formation of a triangle.    we knew they were definitely not stars,  so we continue to observe as they hovered above.   that's when we noticed there were numerous black helicopters all around them.    we were not sure what was going on, but it was spectacular so we drove approximately 2 miles and parked.  we videotaped while we were driving and we videotaped when we stopped.   we were focused on the bright lights in the helicopters that were surrounding them.  just before the lights disappeared, my son said he saw lightning.   i did not notice this.   but when we review the videos, the last 5 to 10 seconds of footage went completely white and the sound got knocked out.   after this occurred, all that was left in the sky where the black helicopters who then began to fly away.  

 the first thing we then after arriving home, was watch the videos.    at this point, we still knew something was going on but we were not sure what it was.   much to our surprise, the videos picked up a significant amount more, than what we saw with our eyes.  not only were there the bright lights,  but there were objects pretty much everywhere.   probably the thing that shocked me the most, was when i noticed that there seem to be the bottom of an in normas object moving slowly over our heads.   at several points during the video,  you can see what appeared to be the lights on the bottom of an object.   the lights were blue and they were in the shape of a parallelogram.    i was astonished at the amount of objects that were all around us that night, that we never even noticed.   


 i will attach some videos and images below.   on the very first picture for example, you can see the blue parallelogram of lights at the very top of the image.   we were so focused on the bright light n the middle of the screen, that we never noticed the blue object above..
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change
content.summary: He saw three bright star like objects hovering in a triangular formation.   then we noticed numerous helicopters.    my son saw a bright light and our self i'm got knocked out for approximately 5 to 10 seconds.  most of what we saw was caught on video.

content.detailedDescription:
The cylinder passed overhead as i was walking my dog right next to my garage.  it was unmistakable.  it had a continuous subdued front and rear white light, traveled completely silent and slowly disappeared into the glare from town.  it gracefully glided over my head as i fumbled with my cell phone to try to get it on video.  the video turned out mostly black but as i moved it i caught it for a split second.  all you really get, unfortunately, is me yammering on about hoping that you can see it in the video.

this was my second definite sighting, and possibly my third within 5 miles of one another.  the first was 24 years ago along with a co-witness.
content.summary: The cylinder passed overhead as i was walking my dog right next to my garage.  it was unmistakeable.  it had a subdued front and rear white light, traveled completely silent and slowly disappeared into the glare from town.

content.detailedDescription: We saw this object last night on our evening walk with our dog around 10pm. looked like a very bright star. orions belt points directly to it to the left...Most people will think its a star until you look closely. its much brighter, is flashing all sort of colors and looks like its spinning. after we came inside we googled it and checked mufon and saw reports from around the globe...Well its back tonight and i'm hoping people with high powered cameras can go out right now and try and take close up photos/videos of this thing and post them online because i've never seen anything like it. if you read this and have high powered photographic/video equipment, please go outside and take pics of it...Definitely seems a bit strange.

content.detailedDescription: Two lights one behind the other approximately 500 feet apart appeared at 45 degrees from the from the southwest. they were weak at 1st and increased in intensity until it was directly overhead. it departed the same way it arrived. it disappeared at about 45 degrees from vertical towards the northeast. there was no sound whatsoever. it didn't look that high in altitude. to guess i would say around 1,000 feet. i watch the sky at night all the time and this is the first time i've seen something like this. i see satellites all the time and iridium flashes. i see meteors and i see the space station. nothing of this nature has ever appeared before period
content.summary: Two lights directly behind each other appeared at 45 degrees increased in intensity as it went over decrease in intensity until it reached 45 degrees the other way and stopped.

content.detailedDescription:
My significant other and i retreated to bed around midnight.  our dog "tank", is a german shepard mix and he sleeps in our bedroom with us in a large doggie bed on the floor.

our bedroom door was open but all the lights were out and shades were down and curtains drawn.  we were laying there talking, about half an hour into our conversation there was a bright flash of white light which lit up the entire room.  we both immediately got up.  we were trying to figure out what it was.   i asked my boyfriend, did that come from inside or outside?  he said he thought from outside.  if it had come from outside it had to have been pretty bright as it lit up the entire bedroom, and as i have stated our blinds were down and curtains shut, and we have the room darkening curtains.

when we got up out of bed to "investigate", our dog who normally stays in his bed was lying half inside the room and half out in the middle of the door way.  i walked out of the bedroom and into the living room, which is just off the bedroom to the front door, tank the dog followed me.  i went outside to see if there were any clouds, perhaps it had been lightening, although we never heard any thunder, but there were stars out, and a clear night sky was observed.

we, my boyfriend and i both sat on the couch in living room, trying to figure out what it could have been.  it was so very bright!  after about fifteen minutes my boyfriend went back into the bedroom, i stayed sitting on the loveseat in the living room, which faces our bedroom.  to the left of the bedroom door is a lamp on a table, that we had turned on.  he went into the bedroom, leaving the door open.  i was facing the bedroom when at approximately 1 am another flash occured, this flash was more of a blue white, while the first flash as white light. lighting up just the bedroom.  so i called out to him from the love seat, did you see that?  he said yes, i saw another flash.  i then said it seems to be only in that room.

he got up turned on the light in the bedroom for the second time and looked all around, even under our bed.  lol.

i finally got up the nerve to go back into the bedroom around 2 am and soon fell asleep.  however, our dog who is normally our shadow at all times refused to come back into the bedroom and slept out in the living room all night.  today he really has not gone into the room, unless one of us is with him.

also, we live off a very busy road, it is normally well traveled at all times of the day and night.  close to us are two factories.  when we saw the flashes both times, we both observed that there was no traffic at all outside for at least ten mins. before and after.  which is strange.  for instance when i went outside to look at the sky the first time, i told my boyfriend, isn't that strange?  where are all the cars?  it looks deserted out there.

because we live in the town, on a busy road i just need to know did anyone else close to us observe anything like this very early this morning?
content.summary: Flash of light observed inside dark bedroom with shades down and curtains drawn

content.detailedDescription:
Filled out at mufon hq, with witness on the phone by field investigator l.Flechtner on april 5th, 2016.


in 1964, during the fall/winter months, on a dark main highway, my father and i were returning home to oilton, from tulsa where we worked. we came over a ridge and has we approached the top we could see a very bright light. the light was so bright it look a football stadium lite up. we saw a white, glowing orb, four to six feet in diameter about 4 feet off the ground following the road on the edge. silently. we followed the while orb at about 40 mph, 50 feet away, for less the 5 minutes.Then it slowly
 rose into the sky and went away. it was a clear cloudless night so we could see it for a long time.
my father was about 40 years old at the time and i was 19. my father had been in the navy and was a trained navel aerial observer. 

in january of 1996 i had another sighting  i was visiting my parents in grant falls, wa. i was about 51 years old.  out side and across the street from my parents house, my brother in law called me outside. he was looking a this big tree and a string of lights seemed to be rising from the ground at an angle towards the sky over the tree. the white lights were like points of light straight above the trees. it was dark and we couldn't see a structure that many have been attached to the light.S we watched them for about one half hour. this was near lake stevens lake.
content.summary: In 1964, during the fall winter months, on a dark main highway,my father and i were returning home from tulsa where we worked, we came over a ridge and has we approached the top we could see a very bright light.

content.detailedDescription:
I was taking photos of a double rainbow, just after a thunderstorm. i took several photos, about 6 . i was directly across the street from the national cometary. i did not notice the object when photographed. i took the film to be developed at the fox one hour kiosk in albuquerque new mexico. when i went through the photos is when i saw this object in just one photograph. 

i took the photo to sun spot observatory in new mexico. they told me that i was about 500 feet from the object. they told me that the object was going at least 500 mph. they told me that shadows were consistent with all other objects in the photograph. they told me that the camera i was using, a kodak instamatic, that this photograph could not have been faked. they told me not to show it to people, because i could get into trouble. i went to kirtland air force base, where a friend of mine was a helicopter mechanic, and i showed the picture to some pilots. they became very angry with me, and told me to get the hell off the base, and that if i ever came back there again, they would report me to base security. one pilot told me that i was a trouble maker, and that he was going to inform base security of my address and have me put in jail. i did not go to jail, and no one ever contacted me about the photograph. about two weeks later, i gave the photograph, original, to a man named dr. greer. he told me that he had friends in the area that would examine the photo and that he would contact me in about two weeks to tell me about what it was. i never heard back from dr. greer. in the past years i have attempted to contact dr. greer, but he has never returned my phone calls. i also sent a copy to a man, dr. stanton freidman. he told me that the photo was interesting.
content.summary: Did not observe vehicle actualflight.

content.detailedDescription:
I was on my way to the store in alamogordo nm. while stopped at the corner of rattlesnake rd.To enter us 54-70, i saw the ignition of the first booster of the start of a test at holloman afb.Hi speed test track.  
almost at the point where the sled started to move, an object popped up from the left flank of the test,but behind slightly.  the object exploded to a larger magenta like coronal ball. this was from a distance of 13 miles.  the plume of the test sled formed a cone of about the size of a pencil eraser at arms length the ball of the corona was proportionally as large. the ball followed the sled down the track for a couple of moments and then followed it on the side for a moment or two then as the sled second thrust came on, the ball followed in front of the sled for a few moments.  by the time the sled got to what is known as the midway (data collection site) the object changed direction from paralleling the track, to a direction aiming almost directly at where my intersection was. at this point of its path it was slightly faster than the test sled, but on changing direction it also accelerated to a velocity that was faster than a bullet.  i had really wanted to see what the core of the object looked like.  all that was left were the heat risers off of the pavement in front of me. i equate that to a stream of water moving gently and having a stone thrown in or looking at an image in a mirror and having the glass of the mirror tapped and the image breaks up. this was late in the afternoon and i was looking to the west and the heat risers were quite pronounced.  the object passed so fast that when i turned to look to the north north east, i saw nothing. it was almost a year later that a friend passed along a report from an investigator from alamogordo that fit both in time and situation.  he explained that a disc had been seen behind a place called round mountain east of tularosa nm, where people coming from the race track in ruidoso pulled over to the side of the road to watch the disc.  suddenly a bunch of probes or drones from all over the tularosa basin came together and attached to the disc.  at this point the disc departed. this filled in a lot of blanks for me. they were spying on the test.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Drone popped up, followed hi spd. test sled, passed, led, accelerated at me, passed in front, dissapeared.

content.detailedDescription: I was driving north on mcclelland rd in canonsburg, pa area seven on your map, in washington county, friday, june 6,2014 around 1:00 p.M.  i was heading north to a doctor's appointment. as i was leaving the bp gas station near the entrance to interstate 79 north, i saw a flotilla of many ufo's flying in formation in the clear blue sky.  they were whiteish-slightly silver discs, three abroad and approximately say eight or nine abreast.  the ufo's were three rows high, eight to nine crafts or rather discs in a long row, flying in three straight lines, leaving chem-trails behind themselves.  the discs appeared more like "cloudy" formations rather than classical flying saucer formations.  as i traveled north, the ufo's looped around in the sky and it appeared as if they were following my car's direction.  they looped around the air now, above rt. 19 north, now i was in mcmurray, pa    now more crafts were in formation keeping their organized three rows.  now it seemed as it there were twelve to fifteen cloudy discs flying in formation. i stopped in my chiropractor's office for my appointment. when i came out the sky was clear. interstate 79 and rte.19 are busy routes, so i know someone else must have seen what i saw. the flotilla was flying north up rte.19 toward pittsburgh.

content.detailedDescription:
Every night between 8 pm and 10 pm i would be observe closely by two separate crafts one off to the southwest and the other one off to the south east. these two crafts would almost park themselves in one spot and hover their night after night.
my dogs would completely flipped out and barking uncontrollably when they were getting near as i peered out my window when craft had turned from running lights along the bottom to a ball of electricity. at the times i looked outside to watch these crafts a shadow appeared in front of my window and scratched my window at the spot my face was. i got so scared i fell back on my ass.
my oldest male dog insisted on staying outside his kennel so he could watch over my bedroom. which indicates he feels that there's something that could be in my room that i would need protection from. i no longer have a period at 39 and they may have been taking my eggs.
what i think is strange is they are focusing a lot of energy on me and as far as society is concerned i'm nobody.
at the intensity of these day-to-day month-to-month counters cause me to feel scared to be alone in my home and when i went to my parents house it repositioned itself in front of my parents front door and that night i wanted to sleep there to feel safe. within 15 minutes my parents were asleep and the craft had come close and hovered over the house i could barely hear it it was similar to a helicopter but quiet and i could feel the vibrations from the engines and i could hear that one propeller was loose and rattling.
i had felt very harassed by these crafts and feared for my life i don't know if they are friendly or not.
after this craft was scene over my house by my neighbors and they reported a ufo hovering very low in town i don't remember the exact day.
these encounters or most intense in late fall and all winter 2015 & 2016.
i would appreciate it very much if someone from mufon spoke to me personally because i have a lot more details to these occurrences considering they happened over several months span
content.summary: I was being observed by two separate crafts over the period of several months.

content.detailedDescription:

"few minutes after my status update on earthquake some time ago, i was looking outside from my friend's window at shillong for half an hour at the far-away massive lightning and the wild winds in action. if i'm not mistaken, i saw a ufo in the night sky just then, in the shape of a disc with three distinct lights,red,white and green, moving in circles. at first, i thought the blinking object was a shooting star and i believed so. then, i saw those lights and i thought it's a satellite but it had 3 lights moving at a speed of helicopter and the shape got more distinctly visible with the lightning like those in movies. it was up there for 5 minutes and went beyond my vision. i ain't crazy and i don't understand why i witnessed this crazy flying object with no sound. a weird day with earthquake, cyclone and a total black out here and an unidentified flying object..... i need some break."

content.detailedDescription: I had just closed up my family business at 7pm, on march 4th, 2016; when i noticed a jet flying high up, over the building, and thought i should test my new galaxy s7 edge phone's camera on a good distance shot.  i took 2 photo's of this jet moving upwards, into the clouds.  in the second shot, it looked like i could see the shape of the jet, so i zoomed in to see how crisp it actually gets, and almost didn't notice the black shape/s underneath.  i believe it to be one object moving very fast, out of the bottom right cloud, and leveling off just underneath the jet.  it's just unidentified!?  what do you think.  oval shaped wingless bug, or ufo?.. you decide!
content.summary: 1 of 2 snap shots of a jet caught 3 black shapes upon closer look.

content.detailedDescription: At exactly 4:01 a.M. i went outside on my balcony to smoke a cigarette. i spend a lot of time looking up at the sky at night, and i have seen many shooting stars. shootings stars move extremely fast and appear to zoom across your range of vision in an instant. the "light" i saw tonight did no such thing. while it did vanish in an instant, it did not zoom across my range of vision. directly in the center of the sky, what appeared to be a large aircraft, lit up in the darkness--without making a sound. it instantly propelled itself into the distance leaving behind a momentary trail of green and orange light. what was most unusual about this sighting was that the object changed direction. the object also moved much more quickly than any shooting star that i have ever seen. i could not determine its exact location or distance. however, initially after lighting up, the size of the object appeared three to four times larger than the stars in the sky. this means that the object was either much larger and/or much closer than our closest stars. after the incident, i felt slightly uncomfortable--as if i had a headache, but only in the front half of my brain.
content.summary: Ufo sighted over central alabama

content.detailedDescription:
I was working in a camp, and at night i would take out my 900 powered telescope to see if i could see any satellites.

when looking in nw direction, i seen a moving object and it disappeared.  that is when i noticed other craft doing the same thing.  at the same time the craft were going in other craft would come out going in a different direction.  in my opinion the large craft that look like a mother ship was very very very large.

i did not know what the object was, but it was doing things that it should not have been doing.  if it was a satellite it would not disappeared.

at the time i sighted this, i wanted to tell every one but thought i bettered not.  i did tell the head cook (my mother)about it, and she came out and took a look, and the head naturalist came and took a look (brain) i do not remember his last name.  i watch till about 4 am and it did not fly away it just disappeared. my mother told me i would have to make my mind up in what i was going to do.

content.detailedDescription:
During the 1980s i was working for a gold mine in the southern end of crescenty valley, nevada near the eureka/lander cournty line.  the night in question we were hauling gravel from a pit in the valley floor.  one time when i arrived at the pit to get a load of gravel the loader operator was standing on the deck of the loader and pointed a light out to me.  it was obivously outside the earth'a atmosphere, or at least several miles above the earth's surface.  the light would travel diagonally down and to the right, then horizonally to the left, back down and to the right, then horizonally to the left, and kept prepeating that pattern several times.  finaly after a final movement down and to the right, it would go up and slightly left so as to arrive at the point of beginning.  it seemed to pause for a second or two at each change in diection.  it would then repeat the manuever, which we watched numerous times before going back to work.  the movements were smooth and at a steady speed, without either acceleration at the beginning of each directional change or deceleration at the end thereof.  considering that the object had to have been in space and the degree of movement, i believe it was covering a considerable distance in a mater of 2 or 3 seconds.  it was dark outside at the time of this observation and i believe it was summer time.  it was in the mid 1980s.

i have often thought about and wondered what we observed that night.  i have considered the possiblity that it was a satelite, but it is my understanding they do not move that fast.  an aircraft could not make directional changes like that, nor would it be able to make the directional changes without accelerating and decelerating.
content.summary: Light in space moving diagonally right and down, the horizonally to left, repeated movements several times, then after going to right and down final time, moved up and to left to startimg point.  repeated pattern several times
